Pre-Game Insights: Botswana doesn’t have any significant status on the international stage, so we could expect an easy win for The Pharaohs.
Botswana has struggled recently and lost their opening game of the qualification to Mauritania.
It has been more than 12 years since Botswana qualified for the African Cup of Nations.
Egypt’s national football team are the most successful team in the AFCON and are coming off a 3-0 win over Cape Verde in their opening game of the qualifying.
Historically, Egypt had the upper hand in their last five meetings against the hosts.
Egypt are expected to be without the services of Mostafa Mohamed and Omar Marmoush.
Mohamed Salah and Ahmed Sayed will lead the attack for Egypt.
